Game.....: NFL 2K2
Origin...: USA - NTSC
Released.: September 16th, 2001
Ripped.......: Commentary & FMV Downsampled

Sega Sports NFL 2K2 hits the Gridiron on the Sega Dreamcast video game console, the PlayStation 2 computer entertainment system from Sony Computer Entertainment America and the Xbox video game system from Microsoft this fall with the look and feel of a champion. With all-new gameplay and platform-specific features, NFL 2K2 combines flash and substance in a football game that is as exciting to watch as it is to play. 

Game Features:
- Online console gameplay - Play head-to-head with up to eight people nationwide. 
- Updated online functionality allows gamers to track their wins/losses to see how they rank among gamers online! 
- True-to-life quarterback logic - QBs act like they do in the pros! 
- Enhanced passing and catching system - Pass play timing and execution is more intelligent and accurate than ever before. 
- New player models with extreme detail - You'll recognize all your favorite players! 
- More player animations - New QB rollouts, improved RB spinning and stiff-arm moves, better grasping and tackling on D, and realistic stumbling for all players. 
- All new commentary - With more lines of dialogue than any NFL video game. 
- Updated rosters, stadiums, and team uniforms for the 2001 season.